==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expectative
<hw>Ex*pect"a*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>expectatif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Constituting an object of
expectation; contingent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Expectative grace</b></col>, <cd>a mandate given by the
pope or a prince appointing a successor to any benefice before it
becomes vacant.</cd> <rj><au>Foxe.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expectative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Expectative
<hw>Ex*pect"a*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>expectative</ets>,
fr. <ets>expectatif</ets> expectant.]</ety> <def>Something in
expectation; esp., an expectative grace.</def>
<rj><au>Milman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expectedly</ent>⟦br⟧
